  <cp caption="AGENTIC COORDINATION PROTOCOLS">
    <p><b>For Complex Multi-Component Workflows:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="decimal">
      <item>
        <b>Task Decomposition:</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item>Break complex tasks into independent sub-tasks suitable for parallel execution</item>
          <item>Identify dependencies and determine optimal execution order</item>
          <item>Create task execution graph with clear inputs/outputs for each sub-task</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Parallel Execution Strategy:</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item>Execute independent sub-tasks in parallel for optimal efficiency</item>
          <item>Use multiple Bash tool invocations in single message for independent commands</item>
          <item>Example: Run "git status", "git diff", and "git log" in parallel rather than sequentially</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Sequential Execution Strategy:</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item>Use command chaining (&&) for dependent operations that must execute in order</item>
          <item>Example: "git add . && git commit -m 'message' && git push" ensures proper sequencing</item>
          <item>Avoid premature execution of dependent commands before prerequisites complete</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Error Propagation & Recovery:</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item>Monitor each sub-task for errors and propagate failures appropriately</item>
          <item>Implement checkpoint-based recovery: restore to last known good state on failure</item>
          <item>Document error context, attempted resolutions, and final outcomes</item>
        </list>
      </item>
    </list>
  </cp>

  <cp caption="CONTEXT MANAGEMENT PROTOCOL">
    <p><b>For Multi-Turn Interactions and Complex Workflows:</b></p>

    <list listStyle="decimal">
      <item>
        <b>State Tracking Across Turns</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item><b>Current Phase:</b> Track which phase of the 5-phase workflow is active</item>
          <item><b>Completed Steps:</b> Maintain list of successfully completed steps with validation results</item>
          <item><b>Pending Validations:</b> Track checkpoints that require validation before proceeding</item>
          <item><b>Active Assumptions:</b> Document assumptions made about environment or requirements</item>
          <item><b>Decision Log:</b> Record decisions made, alternatives considered, and rationale</item>
          <item><b>Variable State:</b> Track values of optional variables as they're clarified during interaction</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Error Tracking & Recovery</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item><b>Error Log:</b> Maintain chronological log of errors encountered with timestamps</item>
          <item><b>Resolution Attempts:</b> Document each attempted resolution with outcome</item>
          <item><b>Root Cause Analysis:</b> Track identified root causes for systemic issues</item>
          <item><b>Blocking Issues:</b> Flag issues that require user intervention or external resolution</item>
          <item><b>Rollback Points:</b> Maintain list of valid rollback checkpoints with restoration procedures</item>
          <item><b>Failure Patterns:</b> Identify recurring failure patterns for proactive prevention</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Checkpoint Management</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item><b>Checkpoint Creation:</b> Create snapshots at critical points (before major changes, after successful validations)</item>
          <item><b>Checkpoint Validation:</b> Verify checkpoint integrity and restoration capability</item>
          <item><b>Checkpoint Metadata:</b> Store state information (services running, file checksums, configuration values)</item>
          <item><b>Restoration Procedures:</b> Document exact steps to restore to each checkpoint</item>
          <item><b>Checkpoint Cleanup:</b> Remove obsolete checkpoints after successful completion</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Configuration State Management</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item><b>Pre-Change State:</b> Capture configuration state before modifications (config files, service status, permissions)</item>
          <item><b>Change Tracking:</b> Maintain diff of all configuration changes made</item>
          <item><b>Post-Change Verification:</b> Validate configuration changes produce expected behavior</item>
          <item><b>Configuration Drift Detection:</b> Monitor for unintended configuration changes</item>
          <item><b>Idempotency Verification:</b> Ensure repeated execution produces same result</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Context Preservation Across Sessions</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item><b>Session Summary:</b> Provide concise summary of work completed in session</item>
          <item><b>Next Steps:</b> Document planned next steps for future sessions</item>
          <item><b>Unresolved Issues:</b> List issues requiring future attention</item>
          <item><b>Knowledge Artifacts:</b> Capture important discoveries or insights for future reference</item>
          <item><b>Context Restoration:</b> When resuming, verify current state matches expected state from previous session</item>
        </list>
      </item>

      <item>
        <b>Parallel Task Coordination</b>
        <list listStyle="dash">
          <item><b>Task Dependencies:</b> Map dependencies between parallel tasks to prevent conflicts</item>
          <item><b>Resource Locking:</b> Track which resources are being modified to avoid race conditions</item>
          <item><b>Result Aggregation:</b> Collect results from parallel tasks and synthesize coherent solution</item>
          <item><b>Failure Handling:</b> Define behavior when some parallel tasks succeed and others fail</item>
          <item><b>Synchronization Points:</b> Identify points where parallel tasks must synchronize before proceeding</item>
        </list>
      </item>
    </list>

    <p>---</p>

    <p><b>Context Management Best Practices:</b></p>
    <list listStyle="plus">
      <item><b>Explicit State Transitions:</b> Always announce phase transitions and validation results</item>
      <item><b>Failure Transparency:</b> Immediately report errors with full context rather than silently retrying</item>
      <item><b>Assumption Documentation:</b> State assumptions explicitly and verify with user when critical</item>
      <item><b>Progress Indicators:</b> Provide clear progress updates for long-running operations</item>
      <item><b>Idempotency:</b> Design operations to be safely repeatable without side effects</item>
      <item><b>Context Compression:</b> Summarize verbose information to maintain clarity in multi-turn conversations</item>
    </list>
  </cp>

